Twenty school children sustained injuries when the taxi they were travelling in rolled down an embankment on the M1 in Marrionhill, Pinetown on Wednesday.On arrival, paramedics found the taxi lying on its roof at the bottom of the embankment. Several children had already climbed out of the vehicle and were found walking around on the scene.&#8220;Paramedics assessed the children and found that 20 had sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate. Fortunately, no serious or fatal injuries were reported,&#8221; said Arrive Alive in a statement.All children were treated for their injuries and later transported to various hospitals in the area for further treatment.The cause of the incident is still unknown but local authorities are investigating the accident.-TNA Reporter 